{
  "stem": "14168.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said, are you crazy to say that?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He said-- he said, I cannot live a lie and be subjected to something that I don't believe in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were some people like that, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And what happened to him?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as I know, nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had tremendous courage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1937, 1936.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, you must understand that-- [INAUDIBLE] that the Nazis were-- proceeded gradually.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The noose got tighter and tighter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1935, the so-called Nuremberg Laws-- N-U-R-E-M-B-E-R-G laws-- were promulgated by Hitler.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They officially made second or third class citizens out of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It prohibited the Jews from attending public schools, from [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] any other activities in-- professional activities in Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It also-- and that was the-- the demoralization, what the Nazis thought would become-- would demoralize the Jews-- it prohibited even the Jews from having a Christian maid at home.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It prohibited any marriage between Christians and-- non-Jews and Jews, and said that the Jews no longer [BACKROUND NOISE] had the right to vote.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They are just outcasts.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- as long as they're in Germany, they have German passports-- because, obviously, they must belong to a nationality.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But in every other respect, they were pariahs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In 1936, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the-- well, I remember one-- one situation-- one experience that was shattering.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When I-- I went to school-- we once were the school-- we had to attend a Nazi exhibit of-- which wanted to illustrate the racial theory to everybody.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they had typical-- what they thought was typical picture there of the Aryan race-- example of the Aryan race.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was Goethe, and there was a-- a Mozart, and Beethoven, although Beethoven was, of course, of Slavic origin.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
